oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photograph postcard of Oliver Ernest Jackson and Jacqueline Leona Price
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Oliver Jackson and Jacqueline Leona Price were engaged before the war. This studio photo likely taken before Jackson left for France, and was given to her brother John H. Price. Jackson survived the war and the couple was married February 9, 1919.
